From: Xingyu Wu <xingyu.wu@starfivetech.com>
Date: Mon, 26 Aug 2024 16:04:30 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] riscv: dts: starfive: jh7110-common: Fix lower rate of
 CPUfreq by setting PLL0 rate to 1.5GHz
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.10.11
Git-commit: 61f2e8a3a94175dbbaad6a54f381b2a505324610

[ Upstream commit 61f2e8a3a94175dbbaad6a54f381b2a505324610 ]

CPUfreq supports 4 cpu frequency loads on 375/500/750/1500MHz.
But now PLL0 rate is 1GHz and the cpu frequency loads become
250/333/500/1000MHz in fact.

The PLL0 rate should be default set to 1.5GHz and set the
cpu_core rate to 500MHz in safe.

Fixes: e2c510d6d630 ("riscv: dts: starfive: Add cpu scaling for JH7110 SoC")
Signed-off-by: Xingyu Wu <xingyu.wu@starfivetech.com>
Reviewed-by: Hal Feng <hal.feng@starfivetech.com>
Signed-off-by: Conor Dooley <conor.dooley@microchip.com>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 arch/riscv/boot/dts/starfive/jh7110-common.dtsi | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/riscv/boot/dts/starfive/jh7110-common.dtsi b/arch/riscv/boot/dts/starfive/jh7110-common.dtsi
index 68d16717..51d85f44 100644
--- a/arch/riscv/boot/dts/starfive/jh7110-common.dtsi
+++ b/arch/riscv/boot/dts/starfive/jh7110-common.dtsi
@@ -354,6 +354,12 @@ spi_dev0: spi@0 {
 	};
 };
 
+&syscrg {
+	assigned-clocks = <&syscrg JH7110_SYSCLK_CPU_CORE>,
+			  <&pllclk JH7110_PLLCLK_PLL0_OUT>;
+	assigned-clock-rates = <500000000>, <1500000000>;
+};
+
 &sysgpio {
 	i2c0_pins: i2c0-0 {
 		i2c-pins {
-- 
